# Test fixture provenance

These fixtures live under `tests/` and are NOT installed or shipped in the
package (`inst/`); they exist only to drive the offline test suite.

Unless noted otherwise below, every fixture in this directory is
**sitemapr-authored, clean-room** content created for this project and is
covered by the package license (MIT). The XML/text files describe synthetic
`example.com` sitemaps; they reproduce no third-party document.

## Schema-validation fixtures (Layer C)

Authored for the schema-validation slice (SITE-qcjvesdw). Each exercises a
specific resolution/validation path against the bundled clean-room XSD
profiles; none is copied or adapted from an upstream corpus.

| Fixture | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `valid-minimal.xml` | minimal valid core `urlset` |
| `valid-index.xml` | valid core `sitemapindex` |
| `schema-invalid-urlset.xml` | misplaced `<priority>` before `<loc>` (invalid) |
| `ns-image.xml` | core + image extension |
| `ns-news.xml` | core + news extension |
| `ns-video.xml` | core + video extension |
| `ns-hreflang.xml` | core + xhtml:link hreflang alternates |
| `ns-all-four.xml` | core + image + video + news + hreflang (runtime profile) |
| `ns-video-invalid-in-mixed.xml` | valid siblings, invalid video child (scoping) |
| `ns-unknown.xml` | namespace absent from the catalog |
| `xxe-attempt.xml` | external SYSTEM entity; must not expand |
